UMASK Values (Root vs Normal User)
Root user default UMASK       # 022
Non-root (regular user)      # 002 or 022 (depends on distro)

Difference:
Root user (022)
Files → 644
Directories → 755
✅ More secure (others get read-only)

Normal user (often 002 in some systems)
Files → 664
Directories → 775
✅ Group collaboration allowed

Where UMASK is Set
/etc/profile
/etc/bashrc
/etc/login.defs
~/.bashrc

